1947;;Song of Love;;American;;Clarence Brown;;Katharine Hepburn, Paul Henreid, Robert Walker;;biopic;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Song_of_Love_(1947_film);;Fictionalized romance in the 19th century of musicians Clara Wieck Schumann (Katharine Hepburn), Robert Schumann (Paul Henreid) and Johannes Brahms (Robert Walker). Clara takes a break from her thriving career as a concert pianist to devote herself to her struggling composer husband Robert. Unable to cope with disappointment and failure, Robert eventually has a breakdown while conducting a performance. He later dies in an asylum, and Clara devotes the rest of her life to preserving his music and his memory.[2]